{"type":"message","id":"6aeb6277","parentId":"ac011e5d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:21:45.902Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cqkorwp03u1t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152116\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and goals. The session has been productive:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. CFI Compression experiment completed with key findings\r\n3. Next pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n4. Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe last pulse was at pulse_2026-03-24 152016.md. The observation notes \"No mutations applied this cycle.\"\r\n\r\nI need to take a concrete action that advances the goals. The pending action is clear: implement the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script that tests the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Or update the existing CFI compression synthesis with the next steps\r\n3. Or create a new document planning the experiment\r\n\r\nGiven the goal is to run the experiment, I should create the experiment script or at minimum document the experiment design clearly. The most concrete action would be to either:\r\n- Create an experiment script to run the hybrid scoring test\r\n- Update goals.md to reflect the next concrete step\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment script that will run the hybrid scoring comparison against binary thresholds. This moves toward the pending action.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified the \"constant format problem\" but the next experiment (hybrid scoring) is still pending. The theoretical foundation is clear: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120), but this needs empirical validation.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid scoring experiment script that tests Strategy C against the binary threshold approaches. This moves directly toward completing the pending experiment.\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Comparing hybrid scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n# HYPOTHESIS\r\n# Hybrid scoring should distinguish:\r\n#   - \"constant format\" tokens: freq≈160, CFI=1.0 → score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (over-threshold!)\r\n#   - \"research trajectory\" tokens: freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score = CFI × (freq/120)\r\n\r\n# Wait - this reveals a flaw: freq=160, CFI=1.0 gives score=1.0, same as research tokens!\r\n# The hybrid formula alone doesn't solve the constant format problem.\r\n\r\n# ACTUAL SOLUTION: Cap frequency input\r\n# score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# For freq=160: min(1, 160/120) = min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0 (WRONG!)\r\n# For freq=136: min(1, 136/120) = min(1, 1.13) = 1.0 → score = 0.96 (correct)\r\n# For freq=60: min(1, 60/120) = 0.5 → score = CFI × 0.5 (penalized)\r\n\r\n# The key insight: freq > 120 gets capped, so constant tokens (freq≈160) aren't helped\r\n# BUT they also aren't hurt. The real differentiator must be something else.\r\n\r\n# REVISED HYPOTHESIS:\r\n# The three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120) is the answer.\r\n# Hybrid scoring alone is insufficient - we need BOTH the score AND the freq bounds.\r\n\r\n# EXPERIMENT DESIGN:\r\n# 1. Apply three-dimensional filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n# 2. Compare against:\r\n#    A. freq-only threshold (freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n#    B. CFI-only threshold (CFI ≥ 0.5)\r\n#    C. Binary CFI×Freq (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n#    D. Hybrid scoring with top-k selection (score = CFI × min(1, freq/120), pick top N)\r\n#\r\n# SUCCESS CRITERIA:\r\n# - Precision: how many selected tokens are \"true\" research tokens?\r\n# - Recall: how many \"true\" research tokens are captured?\r\n# - The filter should exclude \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.0) but include \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\r\n\r\n# Data source: pulses from research/pulse_*.md\r\n# Ground truth: manually labeled \"metaprogramming\" vs \"research\" tokens\r\n\r\n# TODO: Implement token extraction and scoring\r\n# TODO: Run 200-pulse corpus\r\n# TODO: Compare all strategies\r\nfile: experiments/hybrid_cfi_freq_experiment.ps1\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:21:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380105901}}
